{"word":"G4640 - σκιρτάω - skirtáō - skeer-tah'-o - Leap","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">σκιρτάω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">skirtáō</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">skeer-tah'-o</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Leap</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Verb / வினைச்சொல்</span>"},{"paragraph":"வினைச்சொல் - துள்ளு"},{"paragraph":"to leap"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>Akin to <b>&#x03C3;&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03C1;&#x03C9;</b> <b>skairo&#x0304;</b> (to <i>skip</i>); to <i>jump</i>, that is, sympathetically <i>move</i> (as the <i>quickening</i> of a fetus): - leap (for joy).</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}